1
00:01:10,870 --> 00:01:14,380
Let's reminisce the
special times he had.

2
00:01:14,380 --> 00:01:19,160
[Kim Hyun-joong's Story]

3
00:01:20,730 --> 00:01:25,130
Kim Hyun-joong debuted in 2005
as the leader of SS501.

4
00:01:33,990 --> 00:01:37,920
He shined on stage with his
good looks as a flower boy...

5
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:42,800
And became the center of
many of his fans' attention.

6
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:23,750
This flower boy rose to sudden prominence in
the gayo world, but he has an unusual past.

7
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:27,260
I never received allowances.

8
00:02:27,260 --> 00:02:31,880
I worked for money ever
since I was young.

9
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:38,840
I delivered newspapers, pizza, and chicken,
and worked as a waiter. I worked hard.

10
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,970
- I didn't go to school.
- Since when?

11
00:02:40,970 --> 00:02:43,950
I started chicken delivery
when I was in the 8th grade.

12
00:02:43,950 --> 00:02:47,930
I got a raise around $2.50
because I did well.

13
00:02:47,930 --> 00:02:50,670
- How much did you start at?
- I started at around $1.70.

14
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:54,310
- How much did you make?
- I made close to $100,000.

15
00:02:54,310 --> 00:02:56,990
- By working part-time?
- I didn't go to school.

16
00:02:56,990 --> 00:03:00,980
It was like a full-time job, but
how did you make $100,000?

17
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:04,040
- I didn't spend money...
- You didn't spend money?

18
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:05,590
I saved it up for a
couple of years...

19
00:03:05,590 --> 00:03:09,480
I heard you made money
by starting a business.

20
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:15,110
There are those I worked with since
elementary, and we're still friends.

21
00:03:15,110 --> 00:03:21,760
We said if any one of us becomes successful,
that person will start a chicken restaurant.

22
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:27,640
So I started one. It's doing
well and I made some cash.

23
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:32,620
- You own a chicken restaurant?
- You still manage it?

24
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:34,340
We never knew.

25
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:38,190
- I just found out today.
- Me too. What a surprise.

26
00:03:38,190 --> 00:03:45,000
My friend recently wrote an
ad copy. He's an eccentric guy.

27
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:51,720
I asked what he was doing and he wrote
something strange on the flyer.

28
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:57,710
"If it doesn't taste good
then I'm your kid."

29
00:03:57,710 --> 00:04:00,430
That's incredible!

30
00:04:01,730 --> 00:04:03,090
So you...

31
00:04:03,090 --> 00:04:10,950
Usually it would say "give a refund."
First time hearing something provocative.

32
00:04:10,950 --> 00:04:21,400
We said if any one of us succeeds,
and I was the one to keep that promise.

33
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:27,450
We would think he grew without hardships,
but there's more to his sad past.

34
00:04:27,450 --> 00:04:30,450
I ran away from home.

35
00:04:30,450 --> 00:04:32,190
How old were you?

36
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:35,630
It's when I just
entered high school.

37
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:40,700
It's when Seo Taiji released
a song titled "Ultramania."

38
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:46,090
It drew out my defiance.

39
00:04:46,090 --> 00:04:49,920
- Ultramania?
- I became one.

40
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:53,360
I ran away saying that
I'm sticking to music.

41
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:59,480
"School or music?" "Music. I'll make
money on my own and live well off."

42
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:03,850
But I was cold and hungry.
I almost died 3 times.

43
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:07,280
[Almost died 3 times?]

44
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:13,340
I ran away and ran out of money.
I thought I would die of starvation.

45
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:19,570
My friend told me to stay at his place,
but he was living with his father.

46
00:05:19,570 --> 00:05:25,520
His father told me to get out saying that
he can't accept someone who ran away.

47
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:30,870
My friend allowed me to sleep in the
boiler room which was a storehouse.

48
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:38,490
I was hungry and was searching the
ground for food if there was any.

49
00:05:38,490 --> 00:05:44,250
I went down, but the roads were twisted
and I couldn't find my way back.

50
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:49,880
I discovered a snack shop at 4 AM.

51
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:54,310
My first thought was
to eat and survive.

52
00:05:54,310 --> 00:06:01,330
I ordered a lot of tteokbokki, odeng,
sundae, and twigim, and ate it all.

53
00:06:01,330 --> 00:06:02,240
You ate first?

54
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:08,910
I felt the Heavens were on my side.

55
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:13,590
That shop doesn't do deliveries
but got a call for a delivery.

56
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:14,960
- At that moment?
- Yes.

57
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:18,390
The person who called always
ordered from that shop.

58
00:06:18,390 --> 00:06:25,400
She said, "I'll make the delivery."
I thought, "I should run for it."

59
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:29,630
- I intentionally made another order.
- So she can go on the delivery?

60
00:06:29,630 --> 00:06:32,130
She needs time to cook the ramen.

61
00:06:32,130 --> 00:06:38,360
I ate a little and ran away at the same time
she left while grabbing some twigim.

62
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,790
[Better safe than sorry!]

63
00:06:39,790 --> 00:06:45,090
- You grabbed some on the way?
- He needs something for tomorrow.

64
00:06:45,090 --> 00:06:53,040
I ran about a mile through the alley and
entered a boiler room in a building.

65
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:57,480
But it was a boiler room of
a big Korean dry sauna.

66
00:06:57,480 --> 00:07:01,520
- It must have been hot.
- It was really hot.

67
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:09,940
There's a ladder there. I climbed up
and opened the lid to the sauna.

68
00:07:13,730 --> 00:07:16,030
I already ate the food.

69
00:07:16,030 --> 00:07:21,210
I opened the lid of that underground
bunker and there were people walking.

70
00:07:21,210 --> 00:07:25,720
- You found a passage.
- I thought I should stay here.

71
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:34,720
First, I took a hot shower, and used
someone else's disposable shaver.

72
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:38,060
Look at the things this
flower boy did.

73
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:44,460
I was caught the next morning and
was kicked out. So I almost died.

74
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:46,820
You almost died because you
were beaten to death?

75
00:07:46,820 --> 00:07:51,650
- No, I almost starved to death.
- Nothing to eat after being kicked out.

76
00:07:51,650 --> 00:07:55,410
Another time, I was almost
beaten to death.

77
00:07:55,410 --> 00:08:02,250
My friend pitied me and bought me a bowl
of pork bone stew. I ate and left, but...

78
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:07,700
That alley was full of tattooed men.

79
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:15,170
Two drunk men picked a fight with us,
"Why are you young'uns here?"

80
00:08:15,170 --> 00:08:19,550
They started beating my friend.

81
00:08:19,550 --> 00:08:22,870
- For no particular reason?
- Because they were drunk.

82
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:27,810
I had no strength, but I ran head on
because I had to save my friend.

83
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:33,790
I held on saying, "Let him go!"
But there was an accident.

84
00:08:33,790 --> 00:08:38,660
It was snowing. When I did that,
he slipped and hit his head.

85
00:08:38,660 --> 00:08:41,810
I did that to a gangster.

86
00:08:41,810 --> 00:08:46,220
- You made him slip?
- I made him pass out.

87
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:51,440
- I was afraid.
- There's one more.

88
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:57,590
My friend held on to the other guy
because we had to make it out alive.

89
00:08:57,590 --> 00:09:05,510
That's when the boss and others came.
We thought we were going to die.

90
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:17,020
But the boss started beating the guy who passed
out. "How can you get beaten by some kids?"

91
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:21,550
I said, "Please stop!
We didn't mean to do this!"

92
00:09:21,550 --> 00:09:25,940
He told me to shut up and
asked who did this to him.

93
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:28,960
- Who did this?
- Thought I was a goner.

94
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:38,840
My friend who wrote the strange ad copy
just came out after using the restroom.

95
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:44,400
I was taking care of the situation,
but he completely lost it.

96
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:50,810
- "What are you doing to my friends?"
- When things were starting to get quiet?

97
00:09:50,810 --> 00:09:55,480
That was before he turned the corner.
He just saw that small group.

98
00:09:55,480 --> 00:10:02,430
He saw a large group when
he turned the corner.

99
00:10:02,430 --> 00:10:13,330
He always acted cool. He took out his phone
and told all of them to come at him at once.

100
00:10:13,330 --> 00:10:18,210
I said, "What are you doing? Don't cause
any more trouble!" He called the police.

101
00:10:18,210 --> 00:10:21,100
"Hurry and come! I'm going to die!"

102
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:25,300
We were saved because the
police came right away.

103
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:29,570
The last one is when
I really almost died.

104
00:10:29,570 --> 00:10:31,570
And the one who passed out?

105
00:10:31,570 --> 00:10:34,170
The police took us in their
car and we were saved.

106
00:10:34,170 --> 00:10:38,040
- Did the guy wake up?
- Beats me.

107
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:40,040
I was afraid and left.

108
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:43,380
You said, "Please stop!"
He slipped and passed out.

109
00:10:43,380 --> 00:10:45,770
He slipped on the snow.

110
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:53,760
Also that winter, I didn't
have a place to stay.

111
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:59,030
All the five story apartments until block 163
were being reconstructed in my neighborhood.

112
00:10:59,030 --> 00:11:04,810
All the tenants were told to move out.
I thought of sleeping in those empty rooms.

113
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:11,300
I slept in block 125. I put a mattress in
the basement that someone threw away.

114
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:20,000
I was sleeping, but it was noisy. I woke up
and everything was demolished to block 124.

115
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,440
They were breaking it?

116
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:32,670
Yes. All the apartments were
destroyed except for block 125.

117
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:34,370
You must have fainted.

118
00:11:34,370 --> 00:11:43,580
I went back home and decided
to go back to high school.

119
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:50,460
Such hardships in life weren't bad
since he gained a lot of things.

120
00:11:50,460 --> 00:11:56,070
Winter break is the season when
you run away from home.

121
00:11:57,140 --> 00:11:59,810
Winter break is the season
to run away from home?

122
00:11:59,810 --> 00:12:05,820
Don't go through hardships but spend
a happy new year with your family.

123
00:12:05,820 --> 00:12:13,510
Your goals are not achieved by running
away. Think of what your mother said.

124
00:12:13,510 --> 00:12:19,120
You'll know it when you graduate
from high school like me.

125
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:25,400
Don't regret it later.
Unpack your bags...

126
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:28,780
He's not detailed.

127
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:33,330
Just stay still at home.

128
00:12:33,330 --> 00:12:38,480
If any of you have such thoughts,
take what he said to heart.

129
00:12:39,310 --> 00:12:42,690
He got over such a past and
became one of the best idols.

130
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:48,080
He became a singer he dreamt of and
showed various images on stage.

131
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:52,420
From his charisma to his liveliness,
he showed many different faces.

132
00:12:52,420 --> 00:12:57,120
He unleashed his potential again
in the drama, "Boys over Flowers."

133
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:10,170
He played flower boy, Ji-hoo, and was the
originator of the "flower boy" syndrome.

134
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:30,550
Kim Hyun-joong's special keyword.

135
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:34,390
[Special Keyword 1]

136
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:37,120
[Flower Boy]

137
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:44,880
[Shortened form of "Boys over Flowers" and also
means a man who is beautiful like a flower]

138
00:13:47,170 --> 00:13:49,830
Maiden Jung Joo-ri!

139
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:52,470
[Burden...]

140
00:13:52,470 --> 00:13:54,340
We're a handsome couple.

141
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:57,400
It's just a nice-looking man.

142
00:13:57,400 --> 00:14:01,020
Yup, just a nice-looking man.

143
00:14:01,490 --> 00:14:04,490
Let's look at your word.
Please reveal your word!

144
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:07,770
I starved.

145
00:14:07,770 --> 00:14:09,200
Fine!

146
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:11,540
["Fine" and "I starved"]

147
00:14:13,790 --> 00:14:17,060
Bachelor Hyun-joong...

148
00:14:18,530 --> 00:14:22,140
- Don't laugh.
- Why's he laughing?

149
00:14:23,470 --> 00:14:26,940
- An old lady!
- Don't laugh.

150
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:29,030
Bachelor Hyun-joong?

151
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:31,040
Don't laugh.

152
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:36,450
How do you feel making
eye contact with me?

153
00:14:36,450 --> 00:14:38,770
- Don't laugh.
- Bear with it.

154
00:14:38,770 --> 00:14:41,140
Don't laugh.

155
00:14:41,140 --> 00:14:43,440
- @#&!
- "I sneer"?

156
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,650
"I sneer"?

157
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:46,630
Fine!

158
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:50,570
Bachelor Joo-ri?

159
00:14:50,570 --> 00:14:52,770
[What?]

160
00:14:52,770 --> 00:14:55,690
Maiden Joo-ri?

161
00:14:55,690 --> 00:15:02,930
You were digging through
the trash earlier. Why?

162
00:15:05,270 --> 00:15:07,800
I starved.

163
00:15:08,730 --> 00:15:14,190
Are you going out with
me starting this moment?

164
00:15:14,310 --> 00:15:19,730
- Take your punishment.
- Bear with it.

165
00:15:20,450 --> 00:15:22,040
We're against it.

166
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:24,300
Fine!

167
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:28,920
She has it!

168
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:31,970
[Cell phone?]

169
00:15:31,970 --> 00:15:36,160
Does she have an ulterior
motive for coming today?

170
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:38,230
- Is she here for a date?
- After the broadcast...

171
00:15:38,230 --> 00:15:42,970
- Is this a dating program?
- Don't give her my number.

172
00:15:42,970 --> 00:15:45,250
It's his number!

173
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:46,800
Thank you.

174
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,450
Do you suggest another
word? What will it be?

175
00:15:50,450 --> 00:15:52,210
"I'm ugly."

176
00:15:55,540 --> 00:15:59,950
What do you think
of your looks?

177
00:15:59,950 --> 00:16:02,530
[She can say anything after
getting his number]

178
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:05,420
I'm ugly.

179
00:16:05,420 --> 00:16:08,940
- That's incredible.
- She's humble.

180
00:16:09,900 --> 00:16:15,240
Should we get married in May?

181
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:17,630
[Butchered]

182
00:16:17,630 --> 00:16:19,120
The bride of May.

183
00:16:20,170 --> 00:16:21,870
Fine!

184
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:26,660
Things are moving quickly.

185
00:16:26,660 --> 00:16:29,720
What's with your figure?

186
00:16:32,020 --> 00:16:34,000
I'm ugly.

187
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:38,150
That attack doesn't work on her.

188
00:16:38,150 --> 00:16:43,980
Bachelor Hyun-joong?
Follow me!

189
00:16:43,980 --> 00:16:48,410
Do you still like me?

190
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:51,580
[Looking straight in the eye...]

191
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:55,320
I don't like that.

192
00:16:57,610 --> 00:17:00,640
It ends with him
not liking you.

193
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:05,240
Jung Joo-ri wins!

194
00:17:06,190 --> 00:17:10,950
- Off to the wheel with you.
- Shouldn't get "shampoo hair."

195
00:17:10,950 --> 00:17:12,340
Spin the wheel!

196
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,190
[Spins the punishment wheel!]

197
00:17:20,740 --> 00:17:22,860
He got "shampoo hair."

198
00:17:22,860 --> 00:17:27,180
[He won the long-awaited
"shampoo hair"]

199
00:17:28,070 --> 00:17:32,250
The president of my agency told
me to never slick back my hair.

200
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:35,780
I will do it exclusively
for this program.

201
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:39,810
Who slicks back their hair
exclusively for a program?

202
00:17:39,810 --> 00:17:44,200
- This is the first time ever.
- Fine. Let's do it!

203
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:49,360
What's wrong Han-young?

204
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:53,620
- Can I try once?
- No, I'm doing it.

205
00:17:53,620 --> 00:17:54,790
Please!

206
00:17:54,790 --> 00:17:57,590
Pour water over his head.

207
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:01,580
Is she actually...

208
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:06,100
Even Hyun-bin?

209
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:11,170
You're going to empty it?

210
00:18:11,170 --> 00:18:16,640
- Don't spill it!
- He's like a eunuch.

211
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:20,260
My first time washing
a man's hair.

212
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:25,260
[Shampoo finished!]

213
00:18:25,260 --> 00:18:28,880
Why are you applauding for that?

214
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:34,580
She acts differently compared
to Bachelor Shin.

215
00:18:34,580 --> 00:18:38,330
- This isn't punishment.
- Is he an emperor?

216
00:18:38,330 --> 00:18:41,920
- Do we have to bow?
- He will show his hair.

217
00:18:43,470 --> 00:18:45,580
[Finally...]

218
00:18:45,580 --> 00:18:47,560
[Every girl's dream...]

219
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:50,990
[Here is...]

220
00:18:50,990 --> 00:18:55,700
It's a punishment but not for him.
He doesn't even get a humiliating shot.

221
00:18:55,700 --> 00:19:01,140
Is this the might of a flower boy?
We have evidence of that power.

222
00:19:01,780 --> 00:19:04,370
I can endure pinches.

223
00:19:04,370 --> 00:19:05,970
- Really?
- Yes.

224
00:19:05,970 --> 00:19:08,040
- Really?
- Honest.

225
00:19:09,050 --> 00:19:10,870
Pinch him real hard.

226
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:15,230
Doesn't it hurt?

227
00:19:15,230 --> 00:19:17,100
- Really?
- Pinch me.

228
00:19:17,100 --> 00:19:18,970
Boom, come here.

229
00:19:20,940 --> 00:19:24,580
I was always curious...

230
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:27,010
[Even though Ho-dong strains!]

231
00:19:27,010 --> 00:19:33,850
Please stand here. People will
think it's fake if the cast does it.

232
00:19:33,850 --> 00:19:38,310
Anyone from the audience?
Who wants to pinch him?

233
00:19:38,310 --> 00:19:45,930
- Me! I want to!
- Hurry! Run!

234
00:19:47,340 --> 00:19:48,890
[This look!]

235
00:19:51,780 --> 00:19:53,330
[Moved]

236
00:19:53,330 --> 00:19:55,080
[Only saw him in her dreams]

237
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:59,230
[Even tears!]

238
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:05,200
She lost her mind after seeing him.
Yes, we understand that feeling.

239
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,970
How can she pinch in that state?

240
00:20:09,810 --> 00:20:12,850
I can pinch him.
I can do it.

241
00:20:12,850 --> 00:20:15,530
Wait, wait, wait!

242
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:19,170
Just stay still!
Are you okay?

243
00:20:19,170 --> 00:20:21,520
I'm okay. Oppa...

244
00:20:22,130 --> 00:20:24,800
We have to go on
with the show...

245
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:27,800
I'm okay. Really.

246
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:31,660
We'll do a reenactment
of what you did.

247
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:35,260
Alright. Will you do it?

248
00:20:35,260 --> 00:20:38,060
Hurry! Come up here!

249
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:41,030
[It's the same]

250
00:20:53,270 --> 00:20:54,910
[Am I dreaming?]

251
00:20:54,910 --> 00:20:56,670
[Boom reborn as an actor]

252
00:20:58,970 --> 00:21:02,070
- Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

253
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:06,330
- You're okay?
- Yes, I am.

254
00:21:06,330 --> 00:21:10,240
Calm down. Can you do it?

255
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:15,700
Even this perfect flower
boy has a complex.

256
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:20,040
- I have a complex.
- What did you say?

257
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:22,370
What's with that voice?

258
00:21:22,370 --> 00:21:28,550
Since it's night...
I'm getting facial hair.

259
00:21:28,550 --> 00:21:35,940
This is normal, but I
used to think it wasn't.

260
00:21:35,940 --> 00:21:41,710
I'm getting facial hair because I'm
growing old, but I can't accept that.

261
00:21:41,710 --> 00:21:45,850
I'm an idol! Why am I
getting facial hair?

262
00:21:48,910 --> 00:21:54,680
That's understandable. It's like
when kids first get armpit hair.

263
00:21:54,680 --> 00:22:00,680
Every time I see that on dramas or
music programs, I can't accept it.

264
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:04,140
I have severe dark circles
when make up is removed.

265
00:22:05,910 --> 00:22:14,340
Why do I have dark circles? Then I have
to quit drinking. I can't accept that.

266
00:22:14,340 --> 00:22:18,970
Since I love playing soccer,
my face became darker.

267
00:22:18,970 --> 00:22:20,650
Because you play ball outside.

268
00:22:20,650 --> 00:22:27,440
My face is dark, but
it's white here.

269
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:35,880
When I see myself after a shower,
I look like a burnt matchstick.

270
00:22:37,010 --> 00:22:39,620
Because you're like this
only up to here?

271
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:47,460
You're just dark here like
a burnt matchstick?

272
00:22:47,460 --> 00:22:56,060
I hated that. So I watch male
actors and singers closely.

273
00:22:56,060 --> 00:23:00,590
"Some of them are definitely
like matchsticks."

274
00:23:00,590 --> 00:23:05,670
And Cha Seung-won is one.

275
00:23:05,670 --> 00:23:07,790
Only here?

276
00:23:07,790 --> 00:23:17,790
Since he films outside often,
I thought, "I'm okay then."

277
00:23:17,790 --> 00:23:19,980
[Even Dokko Jin's a matchstick]

278
00:23:19,980 --> 00:23:23,740
Are you jealous of other celebrities?

279
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:26,590
Of course! Yes, I am.

280
00:23:26,590 --> 00:23:29,830
You're good-looking but jealous?

281
00:23:29,830 --> 00:23:35,340
I get jealous too. When I watched
the movie, "The Man from Nowhere"...

282
00:23:35,340 --> 00:23:42,860
When I watched it at the theatre, the
women went wild when he cuts his hair.

283
00:23:42,860 --> 00:23:51,930
I also think it's cool, but I tell people,
"He cuts his hair that well by himself?"

284
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,790
[Every Korean man thinks that way]

285
00:23:55,790 --> 00:24:00,940
"A killer can cut his hair that well?"

286
00:24:00,940 --> 00:24:05,500
- As if you don't understand.
- I try to find faults.

287
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:13,330
When "Jeon Woo Chi" was popular...
He's very cool and a good actor.

288
00:24:13,330 --> 00:24:21,700
When women say he's cool, I agree.
But isn't his dialect strange?

289
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:24,010
[Feels the same]

290
00:24:24,010 --> 00:24:27,700
- Wow! He's really honest.
- Every man thinks the same.

291
00:24:27,700 --> 00:24:32,010
I acknowledge it but jealous.

292
00:24:32,010 --> 00:24:36,680
It's cute that a flower boy gets jealous,
but don't let it get to your head.

293
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:43,450
Why don't we take a glimpse
into his love life as well?

294
00:24:54,670 --> 00:24:59,960
- When was your first love?
- I think in the 7th grade.

295
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:01,460
- 7th grade?
- Yes.

296
00:25:01,460 --> 00:25:08,630
I suddenly remember you saying that
you couldn't talk to girls at school.

297
00:25:08,630 --> 00:25:12,060
- Is it coming and going?
- What's going on?

298
00:25:12,060 --> 00:25:22,150
Other girls were invisible because
there was this one girl I liked...

299
00:25:22,150 --> 00:25:24,270
Then you should've
said it like that!

300
00:25:24,270 --> 00:25:30,680
I only hung out with guys because I
didn't get a chance to speak to her.

301
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:33,640
How and where did you meet her?

302
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:37,420
After school at a
sundaeguk restaurant.

303
00:25:37,420 --> 00:25:39,670
And you were in middle school?

304
00:25:39,670 --> 00:25:45,600
Old people usually go there
to settle their stomach.

305
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:52,030
A middle school student went there?
What is going on here right now?

306
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:55,350
What's your story?

307
00:25:55,350 --> 00:26:02,070
I happened to eat there with a friend
and a girl came in and ordered a bowl.

308
00:26:02,070 --> 00:26:04,490
- A certain girl?
- Alone?

309
00:26:04,490 --> 00:26:06,410
- In the 7th grade?
- Yes.

310
00:26:06,410 --> 00:26:09,400
- She was with her friends.
- So she was with a group.

311
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:13,220
They would usually go to a
bakery or fast food restaurant.

312
00:26:13,220 --> 00:26:17,940
So I ate there almost every
day for 2 1/2 years.

313
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:24,620
- Did she also come every day?
- No. She came only 2 or 3 times.

314
00:26:24,620 --> 00:26:28,580
You ate there for 2 1/2 years
to see her those 2-3 times?

315
00:26:28,580 --> 00:26:38,250
I would rotate my friends around since
they got sick of eating the same thing.

316
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:41,340
[All to see her...]

317
00:26:41,340 --> 00:26:47,220
- You went with your friends to see her...
- He changed his friends and not the menu?

318
00:26:47,220 --> 00:26:48,840
You must have really liked her.

319
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:52,590
"Can I get a bowl here?
Is she coming today?"

320
00:26:52,590 --> 00:26:53,630
I know.

321
00:26:53,630 --> 00:26:56,640
That's how I felt. She came
in when I was eating.

322
00:26:56,640 --> 00:27:03,020
- You saw her when she came in?
- After I saw her, that was it.

323
00:27:03,020 --> 00:27:05,380
- Did you talk to her?
- No, I just saw her.

324
00:27:05,380 --> 00:27:10,180
You should've been cool and said, "A
platter of boiled beef for her, please."

325
00:27:14,580 --> 00:27:19,720
If a man does something cool like that,
she would be like, "What is this?"

326
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:23,800
"He ordered this for you."
Then she would look at you.

327
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:26,430
And you could say something cool
like, "Enjoy" before you leave.

328
00:27:26,430 --> 00:27:32,660
I couldn't do that because I had to
break my piggy bank to eat sundaeguk.

329
00:27:32,660 --> 00:27:40,940
I ate there until the
restaurant closed down.

330
00:27:40,940 --> 00:27:44,740
- What does that mean?
- Did you work there?

331
00:27:44,740 --> 00:27:54,270
The owner was an old lady and she was
sick. So I helped her move meat.

332
00:27:54,270 --> 00:27:59,020
You got close with her while
waiting for the girl.

333
00:27:59,020 --> 00:28:03,740
- You became fond of her.
- Yes, I did.

334
00:28:03,740 --> 00:28:09,310
So it ended with a crush?
At the sundaeguk restaurant?

335
00:28:09,310 --> 00:28:18,590
I had a friend who liked a girl for 3 years
and we spoke our mind at that restaurant.

336
00:28:18,590 --> 00:28:29,240
On December 31st past midnight before going
to high school, we decided to speak up.

337
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:40,190
We agreed to confess and congratulate the
one who hit it off since we're friends.

338
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:48,030
My friend confessed and it didn't work out,
but fortunately, it worked out for me.

339
00:28:49,710 --> 00:28:52,230
How? What happened?

340
00:28:52,230 --> 00:28:54,950
- She already...
- She knew?

341
00:28:54,950 --> 00:29:00,900
I tried to get close to
her friends to get to her.

342
00:29:00,900 --> 00:29:08,490
I tried to get information from
her blog, find out her birthday...

343
00:29:08,490 --> 00:29:10,630
How did you confess?
At that restaurant?

344
00:29:10,630 --> 00:29:12,590
- No, I called her.
- By phone?

345
00:29:12,590 --> 00:29:15,740
You found out her number?
What did you say?

346
00:29:15,740 --> 00:29:22,360
I made a collect call.

347
00:29:24,170 --> 00:29:27,820
This is where it comes
crashing down.

348
00:29:27,820 --> 00:29:30,720
- Why? Why?
- Huh?

349
00:29:30,720 --> 00:29:33,570
- Students don't have money.
- I didn't have money.

350
00:29:33,570 --> 00:29:36,960
He broke his piggy bank
to eat sundaeguk.

351
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:39,380
I made a collect call to confess.

352
00:29:39,380 --> 00:29:42,400
Since you didn't know
what she would say?

353
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:45,120
What was her response?

354
00:29:45,120 --> 00:29:47,780
First, she said, "Who is this?"

355
00:29:47,780 --> 00:29:50,770
Women know but pretend
they didn't know.

356
00:29:50,770 --> 00:29:56,130
She already knew and asked if I would
like to go to the movies with her.

357
00:29:56,130 --> 00:29:58,610
- She did it first.
- That's how you made it.

358
00:29:58,610 --> 00:30:00,990
We didn't date right away.
We started to know one another...

359
00:30:00,990 --> 00:30:03,670
Did you have your first kiss?

360
00:30:03,670 --> 00:30:06,160
Yes.

361
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:10,800
Sundaeguk led to love. His story on
his first love was extraordinary.

362
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:15,250
But this continued with
other celebrities.

363
00:30:15,730 --> 00:30:19,580
Please make eye contact
with Mr. Ahn.

364
00:30:19,580 --> 00:30:21,960
An expert is looking at you.

365
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:24,430
[Gazing]

366
00:30:26,890 --> 00:30:31,220
What are your thoughts?

367
00:30:31,220 --> 00:30:33,900
If he has dated?

368
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:39,020
Not right now, but
he did in the past.

369
00:30:39,830 --> 00:30:41,600
[Is he right?]

370
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:45,280
- Is he right?
- Yes, he is.

371
00:30:46,700 --> 00:30:50,400
[Mr. Ahn the fortune-teller]

372
00:30:51,650 --> 00:30:53,710
[He's more surprised]

373
00:30:54,710 --> 00:30:57,060
[It was a careless remark]

374
00:30:57,560 --> 00:31:00,440
He just said it and
got surprised.

375
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:04,560
I can't lie, and that's
in the past.

376
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:10,520
- But weren't you surprised?
- You could date freely?

377
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:17,060
I don't like hiding things
so I dated out in the open.

378
00:31:17,060 --> 00:31:20,820
- She's also famous?
- Yes.

379
00:31:20,820 --> 00:31:22,450
How come we don't know?
Why aren't there rumors?

380
00:31:22,450 --> 00:31:25,390
- Did you meet only 2 times?
- She's a ghost. A ghost.

381
00:31:25,390 --> 00:31:27,320
[That's why it says ghost?]

382
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:31,570
- Maybe he's dating a ghost.
- If not, there should be rumors.

383
00:31:33,690 --> 00:31:35,610
I wonder why?

384
00:31:35,610 --> 00:31:38,250
- How long did you date?
- It was short.

385
00:31:38,250 --> 00:31:42,670
- How long?
- A week?

386
00:31:42,670 --> 00:31:46,080
It's not that short.
It was about 5 months.

387
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:51,900
- 5 months? That's not short.
- So within those 5 months...

388
00:31:51,900 --> 00:31:54,830
5 months, huh?

389
00:31:54,830 --> 00:31:57,950
- How many times did you meet?
- Not that many times.

390
00:31:57,950 --> 00:31:59,730
Where did you go?

391
00:31:59,730 --> 00:32:07,170
We went to the movies. I like
fishing so we went fishing.

392
00:32:07,170 --> 00:32:09,790
- You drove there?
- Yes.

393
00:32:09,790 --> 00:32:13,510
Where did you go that
had a lot of people?

394
00:32:13,510 --> 00:32:16,670
Garak Market.

395
00:32:18,010 --> 00:32:19,950
There's a lot of people there.

396
00:32:19,950 --> 00:32:22,420
- We ate sashimi.
- Sashimi?

397
00:32:22,420 --> 00:32:25,720
Did Jung-min and Hyung-jun know?

398
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:28,230
- We never knew.
- We're surprised.

399
00:32:28,230 --> 00:32:31,220
- Who is she?
- We were discussing.

400
00:32:31,220 --> 00:32:35,440
- He's a mysterious man.
- Did you date yourself?

401
00:32:37,470 --> 00:32:40,300
[Going off on a tangent]

402
00:32:41,710 --> 00:32:44,050
The girl is not dating him.

403
00:32:44,050 --> 00:32:48,160
She just met him and he's the
one who's taking it seriously.

404
00:32:49,350 --> 00:32:51,830
Was it?

405
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:56,480
- No kidding...
- He's not back yet.

406
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:59,610
We're curious.

407
00:32:59,610 --> 00:33:03,570
What did you like about her?

408
00:33:03,570 --> 00:33:09,170
I thought she was a Japanese doll.

409
00:33:09,170 --> 00:33:10,820
[Japanese doll?]

410
00:33:10,820 --> 00:33:13,640
I almost put a coin in her back.

411
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:18,150
You know this thing inside stores?

412
00:33:21,130 --> 00:33:26,780
I almost put in 30,000 yen.

413
00:33:28,950 --> 00:33:33,300
- In Japan...
- It's a maneki-neko.

414
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:38,260
Please answer us. What did
you like about her?

415
00:33:38,260 --> 00:33:42,790
She's easy-going and cool.

416
00:33:42,790 --> 00:33:45,910
Is she currently active?

417
00:33:45,910 --> 00:33:49,010
Yes, she is.

418
00:33:49,010 --> 00:33:52,860
Then it's that person I saw.

419
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:55,990
[Eun-ji knows?]

420
00:33:55,990 --> 00:33:57,490
Really?

421
00:34:01,590 --> 00:34:07,720
Excluding Hyun-joong, why don't
the three of you explain to us?

422
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:09,940
We want to know too.

423
00:34:14,050 --> 00:34:17,790
We're curious, but let's
bury the past.

424
00:34:17,790 --> 00:34:20,850
I heard you like Lee Hyori?

425
00:34:20,850 --> 00:34:23,170
It's Hyori.

426
00:34:23,170 --> 00:34:28,130
She's charming.
I like charming girls.

427
00:34:28,970 --> 00:34:30,390
Are your feelings the same?

428
00:34:30,390 --> 00:34:38,990
Since I was a trainee, she was in
the same agency so she's my senior.

429
00:34:38,990 --> 00:34:45,080
She has a very cool personality.
She calls me to a get-together...

430
00:34:45,080 --> 00:34:55,150
She calls me to her birthday party so I
don't feel sad that we didn't hit it off.

431
00:34:56,280 --> 00:35:01,810
His unrestrained and off the wall remarks
about her is also one of his charms.

432
00:35:13,350 --> 00:35:17,360
[Special Keyword 2]

433
00:35:18,300 --> 00:35:20,260
[Oddball]

434
00:35:20,260 --> 00:35:27,650
[One of his many characteristics in
which he thinks differently from others]

435
00:35:27,650 --> 00:35:31,040
We burst out laughing at it.

436
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:33,170
- What was it?
- Gray cropped pants.

437
00:35:33,170 --> 00:35:38,620
You bought 30 pairs.

438
00:35:40,690 --> 00:35:45,280
- I only wear one pair.
- Just one pair?

439
00:35:45,280 --> 00:35:48,190
- I wear what I'm fixed on.
- Just like Andre Kim.

440
00:35:48,190 --> 00:35:49,890
Yes.

441
00:35:49,890 --> 00:35:54,720
I had 30 more manufactured since
it was a discontinued brand.

442
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:57,810
- Manufactured?
- I went to a workshop.

443
00:35:57,810 --> 00:36:05,120
I handed it out as gifts to people that
visited me and now I only have 4 pairs left.

444
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:08,430
- We're getting curious.
- You must really like it...

445
00:36:08,430 --> 00:36:12,690
I just ordered another 150 pairs.

446
00:36:12,690 --> 00:36:14,760
[Shocked]

447
00:36:15,380 --> 00:36:20,770
He's a style icon so it would
have a different feel.

448
00:36:20,770 --> 00:36:22,570
Are you wearing them?

449
00:36:22,570 --> 00:36:28,200
I wore them today and I brought a
pair to give them to you, Seung-gi.

450
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:30,210
- For me?
- Lucky.

451
00:36:30,210 --> 00:36:33,850
I'm curious. Are they jeans?

452
00:36:33,850 --> 00:36:35,020
Are they going to censor it?

453
00:36:35,020 --> 00:36:38,350
- It's sweat pants.
- Oh, sweat pants.

454
00:36:38,350 --> 00:36:40,980
[Wear comfortably at home]

455
00:36:40,980 --> 00:36:43,110
Give him the gift first.

456
00:36:43,110 --> 00:36:45,560
I'm grateful.

457
00:36:47,100 --> 00:36:49,520
Thank you. Giving me
this special clothes.

458
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:53,340
I didn't wash it after practice
yesterday to give it to you.

459
00:36:53,340 --> 00:36:54,870
[A gift that includes
his body odor!]

460
00:36:54,870 --> 00:36:58,540
I have to wear it on the spot.

461
00:36:58,540 --> 00:37:00,700
You have to think
of his sincerity.

462
00:37:02,990 --> 00:37:05,590
- You look good.
- It's nice.

463
00:37:05,590 --> 00:37:09,500
Those pants make you look
good whatever you put on.

464
00:37:13,520 --> 00:37:16,250
[How do I look?]

465
00:37:17,190 --> 00:37:19,610
- Do I look good?
- You look good.

466
00:37:19,610 --> 00:37:23,440
It's good but you look
like a shaolin monk.

467
00:37:24,050 --> 00:37:25,920
[Shaolin Seung-gi]

468
00:37:26,640 --> 00:37:30,730
I think he's warm-hearted.

469
00:37:30,730 --> 00:37:33,300
What are you saying
all of a sudden?

470
00:37:33,300 --> 00:37:40,030
He gives clothes that he thinks is
comfortable to people as a gift.

471
00:37:40,030 --> 00:37:41,950
- Since he gives gifts?
- Yes.

472
00:37:41,950 --> 00:37:44,450
The conversation is unique
since they're both unique.

473
00:37:44,450 --> 00:37:50,510
Isn't it expensive to
manufacture them?

474
00:37:50,510 --> 00:37:52,680
It's so strange right now.

475
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:56,700
Is it cheaper to order them
in bulk of 30s and 50s?

476
00:37:56,700 --> 00:37:59,860
You have to find the right factory.

477
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:04,050
You actually go there
to place the order?

478
00:38:04,050 --> 00:38:07,300
But no factory receives
orders for 50s or 80s.

479
00:38:07,300 --> 00:38:13,670
There's another word to describe him other
than a "flower boy" and that's "oddball."

480
00:38:13,670 --> 00:38:21,930
It wasn't intentional, but let's see the many
episodes his off the wall charm created.

481
00:38:21,930 --> 00:38:24,540
[Living with ghosts]

482
00:38:24,540 --> 00:38:31,690
I believe there are aliens and
ghosts other than earthlings.

483
00:38:31,690 --> 00:38:32,910
Alright.

484
00:38:32,910 --> 00:38:38,800
The five of us started
dorming for the first time.

485
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:46,750
We go to sleep and
hear such sounds.

486
00:38:46,750 --> 00:38:52,000
We thought, "What's this noise."
But we kept on hearing it.

487
00:38:52,000 --> 00:39:00,380
I was surprised because the glass falls
off and breaks once every night.

488
00:39:00,380 --> 00:39:01,930
- In the house?
- Yes.

489
00:39:01,930 --> 00:39:12,260
We're watching TV and, I saw this with
Kyu-jong, the glass falls off and breaks.

490
00:39:12,260 --> 00:39:18,480
We were surprised. I come back
after work and remove my make up.

491
00:39:18,480 --> 00:39:25,830
I'm naked as I dry my hair with the
towel. It's night and really dark.

492
00:39:25,830 --> 00:39:33,590
I'm drying my hair, but I saw a guy
through the towel. I was surprised.

493
00:39:33,590 --> 00:39:39,950
A guy was squatting by the shoe
shelf and looking up at me.

494
00:39:39,950 --> 00:39:43,690
I thought, "Who's that guy?"

495
00:39:43,690 --> 00:39:48,610
Within 2 seconds, I thought maybe it's
a ghost. It's my first time seeing one.

496
00:39:48,610 --> 00:39:52,470
I screamed and ran naked
into the manager's room.

497
00:39:52,470 --> 00:39:57,550
The manager was surprised,
"Why did you run in here naked?"

498
00:39:58,670 --> 00:40:01,860
He was sleeping and
was surprised.

499
00:40:01,860 --> 00:40:03,780
He could have gotten
the wrong idea.

500
00:40:03,780 --> 00:40:07,910
I told him, "Hurry, there's
a ghost by the shoe shelf!"

501
00:40:07,910 --> 00:40:13,570
Kyu-jong and I share a room and
this time we saw it together.

502
00:40:13,570 --> 00:40:20,660
We're sleeping and the male ghost looks at
us from here and the female ghost from there.

503
00:40:20,660 --> 00:40:25,630
We were scared at first,
but now we're used to it.

504
00:40:25,630 --> 00:40:28,350
- Since you see it all the time?
- Yes, we see it all the time.

505
00:40:28,350 --> 00:40:33,750
They're talking with each other, and
Kyu-jong would say, "Go to sleep already!"

506
00:40:33,750 --> 00:40:40,410
When I come alone, they're noisy
and knock on the dining table.

507
00:40:40,410 --> 00:40:45,710
Since I'm used to it,
I shout, "Be quiet!"

508
00:40:45,710 --> 00:40:47,550
- Really?
- Yes.

509
00:40:47,550 --> 00:40:50,070
And then I really
don't hear them.

510
00:40:50,070 --> 00:40:57,610
Since we're used to it now,
we're not afraid anymore.

511
00:40:57,610 --> 00:41:06,540
The manager was tired and went to sleep
and the ghost was lying next to him.

512
00:41:06,540 --> 00:41:12,750
He pushed away the face
saying, "Go to sleep."

513
00:41:12,750 --> 00:41:17,320
He's used to it now. The ghost
got up and went outside.

514
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:24,420
He felt uncomfortable and bought a
tailsman but stuck it only on his room.

515
00:41:25,590 --> 00:41:28,720
We went to Japan and saw it again.

516
00:41:28,720 --> 00:41:41,910
The door's over there, Kyu-jong and I are
sitting here and the others are here...

517
00:41:46,520 --> 00:41:49,330
[The MCs have a weak heart]

518
00:41:55,050 --> 00:41:56,570
[Seung-gi's startled]

519
00:42:00,080 --> 00:42:01,870
That startled me.

520
00:42:01,870 --> 00:42:08,150
I went on a trip with some friends.
We had sashimi and bbq in a cabin.

521
00:42:08,150 --> 00:42:12,650
We decided to find a place
where we could sing and drink.

522
00:42:12,650 --> 00:42:15,210
That's when I first found out.

523
00:42:15,210 --> 00:42:18,990
Seogupyo... Seogupo... Seogyupo...

524
00:42:18,990 --> 00:42:20,060
Seogwipo.

525
00:42:20,060 --> 00:42:23,260
Seogyu... gyu... gwipo.
It was Seogwipo...

526
00:42:23,260 --> 00:42:26,670
- Where are you from?
- Jamsil in Seoul.

527
00:42:27,750 --> 00:42:30,220
[He speaks Jamsil dialect]

528
00:42:30,790 --> 00:42:36,170
There's no such place in Seogwipo,
but in downtown Jeju...

529
00:42:36,170 --> 00:42:41,000
There's a place with a room, food and
alcohol, and you can sing and dance.

530
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:44,590
- It was a nightclub.
- Ah! A ballroom.

531
00:42:44,590 --> 00:42:54,750
We went. Our gang and another
gang went there together.

532
00:42:54,750 --> 00:42:59,120
We drank and had fun.
We also sang.

533
00:42:59,120 --> 00:43:05,390
When I'm drunk, I fall asleep.

534
00:43:05,390 --> 00:43:12,320
I left to use the restroom and came
back, but I don't remember anything.

535
00:43:12,320 --> 00:43:14,640
- You were drunk?
- Yes.

536
00:43:14,640 --> 00:43:22,210
I opened my eyes to check my text
and saw I had 100 missed calls.

537
00:43:22,210 --> 00:43:31,830
I put my phone on the floor after
seeing it and went back to sleep.

538
00:43:31,830 --> 00:43:34,660
All of a sudden, I thought,
"What is this place?"

539
00:43:34,660 --> 00:43:36,040
Of course.

540
00:43:36,040 --> 00:43:42,700
I couldn't see my hands.
It was pitch black.

541
00:43:45,070 --> 00:43:48,390
I tried to calm myself because
I could have been kidnapped.

542
00:43:48,390 --> 00:43:51,950
- You must have been afraid.
- I was scared senseless.

543
00:43:51,950 --> 00:43:56,700
I imagined all sorts of things.
"What if I was sold somewhere."

544
00:43:56,700 --> 00:44:08,330
I turned on my cell phone to see, but it
ran out of battery. I only saw for a second.

545
00:44:08,330 --> 00:44:16,890
I groped around for my shoes and
started feeling my surroundings.

546
00:44:16,890 --> 00:44:23,950
I was feeling around the room
and felt several buttons.

547
00:44:23,950 --> 00:44:27,310
Where is he?

548
00:44:27,310 --> 00:44:29,950
It could be a cold storage.

549
00:44:29,950 --> 00:44:31,830
You shouted, but
there was no one?

550
00:44:31,830 --> 00:44:37,420
I shouted, "Is anyone there?"
But there was no answer.

551
00:44:37,420 --> 00:44:42,920
I pressed the button
and it felt familiar.

552
00:44:42,920 --> 00:44:47,750
Ah! It's the room
from yesterday.

553
00:44:47,750 --> 00:44:50,510
The buttons were from
the karaoke machine?

554
00:44:50,510 --> 00:44:51,700
Yes.

555
00:44:51,700 --> 00:45:00,430
Two groups came together and you
were the only one trapped there?

556
00:45:00,430 --> 00:45:07,970
I searched my memory. I slept in
the right room and not the left.

557
00:45:07,970 --> 00:45:13,210
But they left me and
all the workers left.

558
00:45:13,210 --> 00:45:19,690
I was alone in that
dark nightclub.

559
00:45:21,970 --> 00:45:24,550
Think about it, it's dark...

560
00:45:24,550 --> 00:45:27,590
- It really was like night.
- It's scary to be there alone.

561
00:45:27,590 --> 00:45:29,840
- It is scary.
- What did you do?

562
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:36,990
I had to get out. The only light
I saw was from the exit sign.

563
00:45:36,990 --> 00:45:45,100
I went towards it and discovered
a door, but it wouldn't open.

564
00:45:45,100 --> 00:45:47,400
- Since it's locked?
- Yes, it was locked.

565
00:45:47,400 --> 00:45:52,180
- They don't lock it from the inside.
- It's locked from the outside.

566
00:45:52,180 --> 00:46:01,880
I found a phone and dialed 119,
but it rang from another room.

567
00:46:03,430 --> 00:46:05,360
[It's an extension!]

568
00:46:06,230 --> 00:46:12,530
- As soon as you pressed "1"...
- It was ringing from the kitchen.

569
00:46:12,530 --> 00:46:14,580
"What do I do?"

570
00:46:16,300 --> 00:46:21,840
A Korean Wave star trapped in a
nightclub with his hair in a mess.

571
00:46:21,840 --> 00:46:25,190
If that was filmed,
it would go viral.

572
00:46:25,190 --> 00:46:30,170
I was thinking and started touching
the door. I managed to get it open.

573
00:46:30,170 --> 00:46:35,070
I opened the glass door, raised
the shutter, and went outside.

574
00:46:35,070 --> 00:46:38,180
It was like the raining scene in
"The Shawshank Redemption."

575
00:46:38,180 --> 00:46:43,160
My hair was caked and
my face was swollen.

576
00:46:43,160 --> 00:46:50,990
I got out but didn't have money.
I couldn't go back to Seogwipo.

577
00:46:50,990 --> 00:47:03,090
I made a collect call to my friends, but
they didn't pick up. They were sleeping.

578
00:47:03,090 --> 00:47:10,340
Downtown Jeju to Seogwipo
was around 25 mi.

579
00:47:10,340 --> 00:47:13,150
I thought walking would
be overdoing it.

580
00:47:13,150 --> 00:47:15,210
That's like a marathon.

581
00:47:15,210 --> 00:47:21,860
I sat on the street
like a beggar.

582
00:47:21,860 --> 00:47:23,740
[A waste to call a
flower boy a beggar]

583
00:47:24,800 --> 00:47:29,190
- A flower beggar.
- He sure is one.

584
00:47:29,190 --> 00:47:35,240
I hung around for 1 1/2 hours
and finally made it back.

585
00:47:35,240 --> 00:47:42,560
I found out later on why
I was in that room.

586
00:47:42,560 --> 00:47:48,130
It says "Jaejoong" in front of the room.
I thought that was the waiter's name.

587
00:47:48,130 --> 00:47:51,250
But it was on every room.

588
00:47:51,250 --> 00:47:53,440
- Oh, it's occupied.
- There's people inside.

589
00:47:53,440 --> 00:48:00,840
It means it's occupied.
So I entered the wrong room.

590
00:48:00,840 --> 00:48:04,280
[This was the true nature of that
incident! He's an oddball star!]

591
00:48:05,380 --> 00:48:07,440
Why did they leave you?

592
00:48:07,440 --> 00:48:11,930
They looked for me but thought
I left because I was tired.

593
00:48:11,930 --> 00:48:18,480
When you go drinking next time, sleep
at home even though you're tired.

594
00:48:18,480 --> 00:48:23,230
That's why I call them
over to my place now.

595
00:48:23,230 --> 00:48:28,770
I would go around the country
to find famous restaurants.

596
00:48:28,770 --> 00:48:30,490
- Really?
- Yes.

597
00:48:30,490 --> 00:48:36,580
I went around to find tteokbokki
that pleases my palate.

598
00:48:36,580 --> 00:48:43,560
I sign up at a naengmyun bulletin board
and read reviews on famous restaurants.

599
00:48:43,560 --> 00:48:45,850
That's how passionate you were?

600
00:48:45,850 --> 00:48:51,940
There's over 20 tteokbokki restaurants
in Sindang-dong's Tteokbokki Alley.

601
00:48:51,940 --> 00:48:56,770
I went and ate at each place
over a period of 3 months.

602
00:48:56,770 --> 00:48:58,530
- Really?
- Yes.

603
00:48:58,530 --> 00:49:00,820
You must have had
a lot of time.

604
00:49:00,820 --> 00:49:05,210
- You weren't busy at all.
- We thought you were busy.

605
00:49:05,210 --> 00:49:07,960
You should have come on
this show during that time.

606
00:49:09,420 --> 00:49:12,070
Why eat tteokbokki
for 3 months?

607
00:49:12,070 --> 00:49:14,800
- If we only knew.
- We thought you were busy.

608
00:49:14,800 --> 00:49:17,610
We were waiting for you.

609
00:49:17,610 --> 00:49:21,340
I guess I'll be busy now.

610
00:49:21,340 --> 00:49:26,370
- What place is good?
- Any recommendations?

611
00:49:26,370 --> 00:49:30,760
The best place is where the food
is salty, spicy, and sweet.

612
00:49:30,760 --> 00:49:32,470
Huh? What?

613
00:49:32,470 --> 00:49:34,790
Salty, spicy, and sweet. Why?

614
00:49:34,790 --> 00:49:37,780
Stimulating food is the best.

615
00:49:37,780 --> 00:49:40,280
Plus a lot of MSG...

616
00:49:40,280 --> 00:49:42,580
[A devotee of MSG?]

617
00:49:44,600 --> 00:49:48,160
People are avoiding that and
looking for green foods.

618
00:49:48,160 --> 00:49:53,130
Well... umm... I'm taking
medication anyways.

619
00:49:54,450 --> 00:50:03,560
He has unique values. We can find
such charm in the things he says.

620
00:50:03,560 --> 00:50:05,860
- He must've been a rascal.
- I sure was.

621
00:50:05,860 --> 00:50:08,790
I skipped school and played soccer.

622
00:50:08,790 --> 00:50:20,180
Your parents are called for too many
absences and you could get expelled.

623
00:50:20,180 --> 00:50:27,230
I stole the roll book and dropped
it between the apartment elevator.

624
00:50:27,230 --> 00:50:30,100
The space between the door?

625
00:50:30,100 --> 00:50:33,170
- That space?
- Yes.

626
00:50:36,550 --> 00:50:39,330
How do you recover it?

627
00:50:39,330 --> 00:50:43,370
When the apartment
is reconstructed.

628
00:50:45,440 --> 00:50:47,420
[They suffered from H1N1]

629
00:50:47,420 --> 00:50:51,210
- You know, right?
- Of course, I do.

630
00:50:51,210 --> 00:50:58,220
It says in the article, "Celebrity No. 1."
It's not like we're Robot Taekwon V.

631
00:50:58,220 --> 00:51:01,300
[Not regarding sick people's feelings]

632
00:51:01,300 --> 00:51:08,430
- Seung-gi, were you No. 5?
- I was around No. 10.

633
00:51:08,430 --> 00:51:10,090
[Accompanied by backup dancers!]

634
00:51:40,390 --> 00:51:43,060
[He's cool]

635
00:51:53,150 --> 00:51:56,800
[High-class dancing]

636
00:52:03,150 --> 00:52:05,160
[A beautiful finish]

637
00:52:06,890 --> 00:52:09,210
I was curious about something.

638
00:52:09,210 --> 00:52:10,040
What?

639
00:52:10,040 --> 00:52:13,440
Why is there no mic
on the mic stand?

640
00:52:13,440 --> 00:52:14,770
I thought you gave your all.

641
00:52:14,770 --> 00:52:17,910
- I took it off.
- Why?

642
00:52:17,910 --> 00:52:21,890
It's heavy.

643
00:52:21,890 --> 00:52:23,990
[No pretense! He's honest!]

644
00:52:23,990 --> 00:52:27,390
I lost weight due to that while
filming the music video.

645
00:52:27,390 --> 00:52:33,280
- Because you held something heavy?
- Well, it is a lump of metal.

646
00:52:37,710 --> 00:52:40,630
I wanted to be a PR Ambassador.

647
00:52:40,630 --> 00:52:41,610
Huh?

648
00:52:41,610 --> 00:52:47,040
- You know... promoting things.
- Like the Pyeongchang Olympics?

649
00:52:47,040 --> 00:52:50,330
- Like a public service announcement?
- To enhance national prestige.

650
00:52:50,330 --> 00:53:01,010
I don't know about others, but doing
that is representing South Korea.

651
00:53:01,010 --> 00:53:09,530
Then look at the camera and say something
for Visit Korea Year, also in English.

652
00:53:09,530 --> 00:53:14,470
A Korean Wave star can do that.
In Japanese too if you can.

653
00:53:14,470 --> 00:53:19,220
Please visit Korea on
Visit Korea Year.

654
00:53:19,220 --> 00:53:21,000
With confidence.

655
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:24,290
Visit Anus...

656
00:53:24,980 --> 00:53:28,210
[He was nervous]

657
00:53:30,230 --> 00:53:32,290
Visit Anus Year?

658
00:53:32,290 --> 00:53:39,010
It's not Visit Anus Year.
That's not really...

659
00:53:39,010 --> 00:53:42,530
- That's like saying get an endoscope.
- That's the surgery department.

660
00:53:45,210 --> 00:53:48,090
- I'm not confident.
- It's okay.

661
00:53:49,170 --> 00:53:53,540
Please visit Korea on
Visit Korea Year. Thank you.

662
00:53:53,540 --> 00:53:57,480
In English.

663
00:54:16,910 --> 00:54:20,410
Kim Hyun-joong's shining
stage as a solo artist.

664
00:54:20,410 --> 00:54:24,130
[Kim Hyun-joong's Shining Stage]

665
00:54:25,070 --> 00:54:28,710
Kim Hyun-joong announces his
first solo album in 2011.

666
00:54:28,710 --> 00:54:34,820
He presents himself as more mature
as a solo artist with the song, "Please."

667
00:54:47,180 --> 00:54:53,120
[A sentimental pop R&B with a beautiful piano
melody, grand orchestra, and sad lyrics]

668
00:54:53,120 --> 00:54:56,190
[The performance along the
sad song stands out]

669
00:54:56,190 --> 00:55:02,210
[It was changed more than 10 times for him.
