676
00:56:17,800 --> 00:56:23,760
[His matured masculinity can be felt in
the title track of his first solo album]

677
00:58:55,970 --> 00:59:02,200
He transformed into a romantic guy in
"Kiss Kiss", an exciting pop dance song.

678
00:59:15,770 --> 00:59:18,760
[An acoustic guitar leads in
this exciting pop dance song]

679
00:59:18,760 --> 00:59:24,850
[His sweet charm stands out different
from the title track with lovely lyrics]

680
01:02:08,970 --> 01:02:13,960
This is when he forms a
special relationship.

681
01:02:13,960 --> 01:02:21,040
It's his agency's CEO who helped with his
solo career, Bae Yong-joon, aka Yon-sama.

682
01:02:32,480 --> 01:02:35,280
Kim Hyun-joong's special people.

683
01:02:35,280 --> 01:02:39,000
[Special People]

684
01:02:39,640 --> 01:02:43,750
What are your thoughts on being
called "Little Bae Yong-joon"?

685
01:02:43,750 --> 01:02:51,660
People think I'll feel bad for being called
Little something or the 2nd something.

686
01:02:51,660 --> 01:02:57,270
If I could only be half of
what Bae Yong-joon is...

687
01:02:57,270 --> 01:03:01,740
It's good to be half of
him popularity wise.

688
01:03:01,740 --> 01:03:07,770
Kim Hyun-joong and Bae Yong-joon
are very close like brothers.

689
01:03:07,770 --> 01:03:16,750
Bae Yong-joon gave him advice on choosing
an agency when he was worrying about it.

690
01:03:16,750 --> 01:03:22,040
Several months ago, people were
calling me "The 2nd Yon-sama."

691
01:03:22,040 --> 01:03:24,440
Are you two close?

692
01:03:24,440 --> 01:03:25,490
Yes.

693
01:03:25,490 --> 01:03:28,600
Well, he is the CEO of
Kim Hyun-joong's agency.

694
01:03:28,600 --> 01:03:30,530
Where did you meet him recently?

695
01:03:30,530 --> 01:03:35,580
In Busan. He was there alone.

696
01:03:35,580 --> 01:03:40,360
I called him that I'll be there tomorrow.
I got on the plane and we had fun.

697
01:03:40,360 --> 01:03:42,310
What was he doing there?

698
01:03:42,310 --> 01:03:44,420
Solitude.

699
01:03:44,420 --> 01:03:46,830
Solitude?

700
01:03:46,830 --> 01:03:53,920
He was doing mind control in front
of the ocean while sipping tea.

701
01:03:53,920 --> 01:03:57,520
You mean self-control?

702
01:03:57,520 --> 01:03:59,920
["Mind control" is a game term]

703
01:04:00,660 --> 01:04:03,610
I played too many games.

704
01:04:03,610 --> 01:04:11,190
We ate and I asked if
he wanted some beer.

705
01:04:11,190 --> 01:04:20,160
He said, "Sure, buy some canned beer.
Let's drink while viewing the ocean."

706
01:04:20,160 --> 01:04:26,640
But the spring winds are cold. After
2 minutes, he said, "Let's go inside."

707
01:04:26,640 --> 01:04:30,210
He was cold after
experiencing solitude?

708
01:04:30,210 --> 01:04:32,630
He said it's hard
to endure the cold.

709
01:04:34,600 --> 01:04:38,700
Yon-sama can overcome
anything except the cold.

710
01:04:38,700 --> 01:04:42,600
Tell us how you stabbed
him in the back.

711
01:04:42,600 --> 01:04:45,870
I sang the theme song of the
Guangzhou 2010 Asian Games.

712
01:04:45,870 --> 01:04:50,340
[Singing the theme song of the Guangzhou 2010
Asian Games as one of Asia's top artists]

713
01:04:51,570 --> 01:05:02,090
I was waiting at the airport, but someone
asked me in Chinese for an autograph...

714
01:05:02,090 --> 01:05:04,770
Handing me a photo of Bae Yong-joon.

715
01:05:04,770 --> 01:05:06,540
- A Chinese person?
- Yes.

716
01:05:06,540 --> 01:05:15,830
If it was a Japanese person, although not
fluent, I could say, "I'm not Yon-sama."

717
01:05:15,830 --> 01:05:21,320
But this person was speaking in
Chinese and I didn't know what to say.

718
01:05:21,320 --> 01:05:26,770
I kept on saying, "No! No! No,
Bae Yong-joon. No, Bae Yong-joon."

719
01:05:26,770 --> 01:05:32,100
- That person said I was lying.
- Because you're Bae Yong-joon?

720
01:05:32,100 --> 01:05:37,640
This person followed me around the
duty-free shops for 30 minutes.

721
01:05:37,640 --> 01:05:42,280
I told that person that I'm not
him. I'm not Bae Yong-joon.

722
01:05:42,280 --> 01:05:45,020
Later that person got angry.

723
01:05:45,020 --> 01:05:48,800
A star should say he can't sign
an autograph. Why is he lying.

724
01:05:48,800 --> 01:05:50,100
That person was offended.

725
01:05:50,100 --> 01:05:56,720
That person said bad things about
Bae Yong-joon in the end and left.

726
01:05:56,720 --> 01:06:01,770
- That Bae Yong-joon is bad?
- Yes, so he lost a fan.

727
01:06:01,770 --> 01:06:03,340
[He sure is an oddball]

728
01:06:05,160 --> 01:06:08,970
Bae Yong-joon got a bad
name for no reason.

729
01:06:08,970 --> 01:06:15,360
You could have said that you're
singer Kim Hyun-joong.

730
01:06:15,360 --> 01:06:18,000
It's a difference in education.

731
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:22,870
I made him lose a fan due to
me not being educated.

732
01:06:22,870 --> 01:06:28,290
That person will still think you're
him and that he's unmannered...

733
01:06:28,290 --> 01:06:33,770
- Doesn't even sign autographs...
- Doesn't say that he is Bae Yong-joon.

734
01:06:33,770 --> 01:06:37,390
That person might watch this show
and think he's Bae Yong-joon.

735
01:06:37,390 --> 01:06:38,620
[I'm Kim Hyun-joong]

736
01:06:40,060 --> 01:06:45,980
You two seem close. Did you ask
if you could call him on the show?

737
01:06:45,980 --> 01:06:52,390
The writers asked me if
a call was possible.

738
01:06:52,390 --> 01:06:53,930
Of course!

739
01:06:53,930 --> 01:06:59,690
This was my first request. I asked
him, "I have a favor to ask of you."

740
01:06:59,690 --> 01:07:04,990
"I'm going to be a guest on this show.
Is it possible for me to call you?"

741
01:07:04,990 --> 01:07:11,390
He said, "Sure, since this
is your first favor."

742
01:07:11,390 --> 01:07:19,330
- You know "Sebaku"?
- You mean "Sebakwi"?

743
01:07:19,330 --> 01:07:21,510
It's "Sebakwi."

744
01:07:21,510 --> 01:07:27,250
He was confused and said,
"I'm nervous of quizzes."

745
01:07:27,250 --> 01:07:29,380
[He barely appeared on variety
shows and was nervous]

746
01:07:31,780 --> 01:07:41,680
I said, "Just be yourself." He texted he's
nervous on quizzes with a crying emoticon.

747
01:07:41,680 --> 01:07:44,280
[This Korean Wave star
is actually a cutie]

748
01:07:44,920 --> 01:07:49,090
Are we able to call
him on this show?

749
01:07:49,090 --> 01:07:51,400
Should I try?

750
01:07:51,400 --> 01:07:53,070
That's cool!

751
01:07:53,560 --> 01:07:56,460
We're grateful but...

752
01:07:56,460 --> 01:08:04,660
If he does pick up, we're doing
a 1 minute speed quiz.

753
01:08:04,660 --> 01:08:05,720
[A clock's prepared!]

754
01:08:07,990 --> 01:08:14,320
[Calling]

755
01:08:14,320 --> 01:08:17,990
Hello?

756
01:08:17,990 --> 01:08:21,160
Who's calling?

757
01:08:21,160 --> 01:08:22,780
[It's him!]

758
01:08:22,780 --> 01:08:24,210
Start!

759
01:08:24,210 --> 01:08:27,310
You only have a minute.

760
01:08:27,310 --> 01:08:33,040
- The group I started...
- SS501.

761
01:08:33,040 --> 01:08:36,350
- National MC is...
- Kang Ho-dong.

762
01:08:36,350 --> 01:08:39,460
- Huh?
- Kang Ho-dong.

763
01:08:39,460 --> 01:08:45,650
Wrong.

764
01:08:45,650 --> 01:08:48,460
What are you called in Japan?

765
01:08:48,460 --> 01:08:54,130
Me? Yon-sama...

766
01:08:54,130 --> 01:08:57,580
The most handsome
in Super Junior.

767
01:08:57,580 --> 01:09:01,680
Umm... Shindong.

768
01:09:01,680 --> 01:09:04,860
President to elementary
school students.

769
01:09:04,860 --> 01:09:07,060
- Hyun-joong?
- Yes?

770
01:09:07,060 --> 01:09:11,470
This isn't a quiz show, right?

771
01:09:11,470 --> 01:09:13,170
[Stop pretending!]

772
01:09:14,500 --> 01:09:16,740
Correct!

773
01:09:16,740 --> 01:09:20,150
Hello, Bae Yong-joon?

774
01:09:20,150 --> 01:09:23,260
Hello.

775
01:09:23,260 --> 01:09:24,480
[A pleasure]

776
01:09:26,680 --> 01:09:29,720
Please greet the viewers.

777
01:09:29,720 --> 01:09:35,800
Sure. Hello, viewers.
I am Bae Yong-joon.

778
01:09:35,800 --> 01:09:37,200
[Charisma can be felt
in his voice!]

779
01:09:37,200 --> 01:09:39,870
It's the same voice you
hear on television.

780
01:09:40,680 --> 01:09:44,600
Hyun-joong said you get
nervous on quizzes.

781
01:09:44,600 --> 01:09:52,340
I thought I had to solve questions,
but I found out it wasn't.

782
01:09:52,340 --> 01:09:55,320
Were you confused with "Sebakwi"?

783
01:09:55,320 --> 01:09:59,780
Umm... well... yeah...
I think so.

784
01:09:59,780 --> 01:10:01,770
[That can happen since he's busy]

785
01:10:01,770 --> 01:10:05,410
What do you think of
Kim Hyun-joong?

786
01:10:05,410 --> 01:10:15,710
He's talented. People with talent
don't make an effort, but he does.

787
01:10:15,710 --> 01:10:24,030
He's always concerned, progresses,
and is always polite and humble.

788
01:10:24,030 --> 01:10:28,520
Many people, including myself,
like that about him.

789
01:10:28,520 --> 01:10:32,210
Why did you go to Busan alone?

790
01:10:32,210 --> 01:10:34,300
- Busan?
- Yes.

791
01:10:34,300 --> 01:10:38,200
I had no place to stay in Seoul.

792
01:10:38,200 --> 01:10:41,210
You can stay at my place!

793
01:10:41,210 --> 01:10:44,180
- Who are you?
- I'm Jung Joo-ri.

794
01:10:44,180 --> 01:10:47,960
- Oh! Hello.
- You know me?

795
01:10:47,960 --> 01:10:51,040
Stay at my place.
It's Hapjeong.

796
01:10:51,040 --> 01:10:52,140
[What a fool]

797
01:10:53,150 --> 01:10:55,470
I heard you get cold easily.

798
01:10:55,470 --> 01:10:59,430
Yes... I do.

799
01:10:59,430 --> 01:11:01,960
How did you know?

800
01:11:03,820 --> 01:11:07,270
Hyun-joong told us a little.

801
01:11:07,270 --> 01:11:10,830
You'll be surprised when
you watch this show.

802
01:11:10,830 --> 01:11:22,410
During the quiz, you said Kang Ho-dong
was the national MC without hesitation.

803
01:11:22,410 --> 01:11:27,230
Since he's there...

804
01:11:27,230 --> 01:11:29,490
[He's considerate!]

805
01:11:30,330 --> 01:11:33,130
During "Happy Together",
he'll say it's Yoo Jae-suk.

806
01:11:34,280 --> 01:11:36,480
What were you doing?

807
01:11:36,480 --> 01:11:38,920
- Me?
- Right now.

808
01:11:38,920 --> 01:11:41,320
I was waiting for this call.

809
01:11:41,320 --> 01:11:44,180
[Even Korean Wave stars get
nervous for getting a call]

810
01:11:44,180 --> 01:11:47,540
- While studying for the quiz.
- His answer was one-dimensional.

811
01:11:47,540 --> 01:11:53,340
We're having a talk battle
for the King of Kings.

812
01:11:53,340 --> 01:11:59,120
Kim Hyun-joong and U-know Yunho
are battling in Round 1.

813
01:11:59,120 --> 01:12:04,950
Could you tell us who you predict
is going to be the winner?

814
01:12:04,950 --> 01:12:08,250
- Umm...
- Could you...

815
01:12:08,250 --> 01:12:16,070
I think Hyun-joong is going to win,
but it's good to see him lose as well.

816
01:12:17,260 --> 01:12:18,820
Why?

817
01:12:18,820 --> 01:12:22,340
I think the viewers would enjoy
seeing him get stood up.

818
01:12:22,340 --> 01:12:24,950
[Puts a lot of thought
into his answers]

819
01:12:24,950 --> 01:12:27,220
Please greet before you go.

820
01:12:27,220 --> 01:12:35,750
I was glad to meet the two MCs even
though it was by phone. I had a fun time.

821
01:12:35,750 --> 01:12:42,850
I hope the viewers will take interest
in this show and always stay healthy.

822
01:12:42,850 --> 01:12:45,730
[Thank you for answering the call
despite your busy schedule]

823
01:12:45,730 --> 01:12:48,540
- Thank you.
- Don't mention it.

824
01:12:48,540 --> 01:12:52,210
Yong-joon, I love...
Did he hang up?

825
01:12:52,210 --> 01:12:54,840
Thank you.

826
01:12:55,400 --> 01:13:01,430
A phone connection for Kim Hyun-joong,
but there were others that pleased him.

827
01:13:01,430 --> 01:13:04,610
It's the people at his agency.

828
01:13:04,610 --> 01:13:07,640
I'm close to 4 types of people.

829
01:13:07,640 --> 01:13:19,690
1st is dancers, 2nd is friends, 3rd is my
old trainees, and 4th is my agency people.

830
01:13:19,690 --> 01:13:28,160
Except for the agency people, the
rest of the 3 types were all nice.

831
01:13:28,160 --> 01:13:35,270
They're nice but not that nice
when nice people saw them.

832
01:13:35,270 --> 01:13:37,590
- Huh?
- That's hard.

833
01:13:37,590 --> 01:13:41,510
Then is Seung-gi nice or what?

834
01:13:41,510 --> 01:13:45,270
He sulks easily.

835
01:13:45,270 --> 01:13:46,800
[Holds a grudge?]

836
01:13:49,180 --> 01:13:54,190
There was an opportunity for me to
get close with my agency people.

837
01:13:54,190 --> 01:13:59,070
I've been there for 1 1/2 years, but I wasn't
close with them for a year and 3 months.

838
01:13:59,070 --> 01:14:03,700
With the exception of the director, Mr. Shin.
You wouldn't know even if I told you.

839
01:14:03,700 --> 01:14:07,370
No, we wouldn't know.

840
01:14:07,370 --> 01:14:18,300
I recently came back from my Asia Tour.
I went to 9-10 countries without rest.

841
01:14:18,300 --> 01:14:24,840
I never went outside this time.
Many fans were waiting in the lobby.

842
01:14:24,840 --> 01:14:30,430
I felt there might be an accident if I leave
and the agency told me to stay in the hotel.

843
01:14:30,430 --> 01:14:34,430
I have nothing to do,
so we drank wine.

844
01:14:34,430 --> 01:14:39,740
We decided to do something to
the one who passed out first.

845
01:14:39,740 --> 01:14:41,260
Do what?

846
01:14:41,260 --> 01:14:43,490
I didn't know what that was.

847
01:14:43,490 --> 01:14:51,010
I thought they were boring people
and the most they would do is tickle.

848
01:14:51,010 --> 01:14:57,920
One person left around 3 AM.

849
01:14:57,920 --> 01:15:04,640
- Back to the room?
- He was dead drunk.

850
01:15:04,640 --> 01:15:08,890
He lost it...

851
01:15:08,890 --> 01:15:14,450
- Don't you mean knocked out?
- Oh! Yeah, you're right.

852
01:15:14,450 --> 01:15:16,160
[Made a mistake!]

853
01:15:16,160 --> 01:15:20,790
Losing it and knocked out
is a big difference.

854
01:15:20,790 --> 01:15:26,700
He was knocked out, but I didn't
know they were such fun people.

855
01:15:26,700 --> 01:15:33,640
They started drawing on his face.

856
01:15:33,640 --> 01:15:38,990
They told me it's okay for me to
reveal those pictures on this show.

857
01:15:38,990 --> 01:15:40,190
Really?

858
01:15:40,190 --> 01:15:45,350
- They said it was okay.
- But not you, right?

859
01:15:45,350 --> 01:15:49,330
I never get drunk with them.

860
01:15:49,330 --> 01:15:52,970
I might retire early.

861
01:15:52,970 --> 01:15:55,060
[He might retire if such
pictures are taken!]

862
01:15:55,060 --> 01:15:57,030
Anyways, I will show
those pictures.

863
01:15:57,030 --> 01:16:01,920
They're not celebrities, right?

864
01:16:01,920 --> 01:16:05,170
I'll reveal them.

865
01:16:05,170 --> 01:16:09,890
- Such things at the agency...
- How shocking is it?

866
01:16:11,470 --> 01:16:13,230
[First scapegoat!]

867
01:16:13,230 --> 01:16:15,180
[What a sight!]

868
01:16:15,180 --> 01:16:17,150
What is that on his body?

869
01:16:17,150 --> 01:16:19,030
This is...

870
01:16:19,030 --> 01:16:21,660
Wow!

871
01:16:21,660 --> 01:16:26,480
- Is he sleeping?
- That is sick!

872
01:16:26,480 --> 01:16:28,570
[Second shocking photo!]

873
01:16:28,570 --> 01:16:30,750
[OMG!]

874
01:16:30,750 --> 01:16:33,080
[As if special effects
make up was applied]

875
01:16:33,080 --> 01:16:34,550
[Funny seeing it again]

876
01:16:34,550 --> 01:16:36,930
And?

877
01:16:36,930 --> 01:16:38,890
[Third and final photo!]

878
01:16:40,280 --> 01:16:44,470
I thought he was Lee Juck.

879
01:16:44,470 --> 01:16:47,050
Seems like he came
back from a war.

880
01:16:49,010 --> 01:16:53,100
They have a sense of honor to throw
away their portrait rights for him.

881
01:16:53,100 --> 01:16:58,910
They sure are a unique family with
strong ties to this oddball star.

882
01:16:58,910 --> 01:17:00,710
It wasn't much...

883
01:17:00,710 --> 01:17:07,130
Above all else, his family
is his greatest support.

884
01:17:07,130 --> 01:17:13,610
It's been several months since I left, but
she prepared a meal as if I never left.

885
01:17:13,610 --> 01:17:19,630
After six months you're like, "Mom, I'm home."
She says, "You hungry?" You're like, "Yes."

886
01:17:19,630 --> 01:17:22,030
After you're done, she
says, "Sweet dreams."

887
01:17:22,030 --> 01:17:25,450
It was awkward. It wasn't
what I was expecting.

888
01:17:25,450 --> 01:17:28,580
You must have told your family
about these things.

889
01:17:28,580 --> 01:17:29,500
I didn't.

890
01:17:29,500 --> 01:17:31,920
Because they'll be worried?

891
01:17:31,920 --> 01:17:37,600
As a global star are you affectionate
to your parents and give gifts?

892
01:17:37,600 --> 01:17:45,730
I'm not affectionate. I received some
exposure and ran away from home...

893
01:17:48,320 --> 01:17:51,310
My family were against
what I was doing.

894
01:17:51,310 --> 01:17:57,680
I give them allowances, but...

895
01:17:57,680 --> 01:18:03,990
I give it to my brother and
tell him to give it to them.

896
01:18:03,990 --> 01:18:06,750
- You can't give it directly?
- No, I can't do that.

897
01:18:06,750 --> 01:18:15,030
I have a lot of worries. I want to
buy my dad a nice foreign car...

898
01:18:15,030 --> 01:18:26,330
If he drives that to Dongdaemun Market,
where he works, people might badmouth him.

899
01:18:26,330 --> 01:18:33,550
I have a lot of stress because I want
to express my heart, but I can't.

900
01:18:33,550 --> 01:18:41,930
That can turn to deep resentment
since parents are waiting for it.

901
01:18:41,930 --> 01:18:52,280
My grandmother fell and broke her leg, and
was paralyzed during the leg operation.

902
01:18:52,280 --> 01:18:57,680
She passed away last year during
the year-end awards ceremony.

903
01:18:57,680 --> 01:19:04,520
After the ceremony, they changed
my bow tie to a black tie.

904
01:19:04,520 --> 01:19:14,440
That's when I felt that I should express more
often because it's too late when that happens.

905
01:19:14,440 --> 01:19:21,240
I had a lot of stress and couldn't call
them because of work on my solo album...

906
01:19:21,240 --> 01:19:24,210
But I should call them more often
after listening to what Yunho said.

907
01:19:26,150 --> 01:19:28,840
[Say, "I love you," to your
father in the morning]

908
01:19:30,100 --> 01:19:35,070
Since we brought this up, why don't
you say something to your father?

909
01:19:35,070 --> 01:19:37,900
Tell him you'll express more often.

910
01:19:38,870 --> 01:19:51,660
I always respected you. I always
act cold and serious to you, but...

911
01:19:51,660 --> 01:19:57,970
That's not my true heart. I apologize
for acting differently from how I feel.

912
01:19:57,970 --> 01:20:07,700
I exist because of you. I'll do well
for you and the family. I love you.

913
01:20:20,090 --> 01:20:22,800
Lucky guy, Kim Hyun-joong,
enjoys the stage.

914
01:20:22,800 --> 01:20:26,660
[Lucky Guy, Kim Hyun-joong]

915
01:20:29,930 --> 01:20:33,870
He releases his 2nd solo
album in October 2011.

916
01:20:33,870 --> 01:20:38,820
He presented his special performance
through the title track, "Lucky Guy."

917
01:20:40,040 --> 01:20:49,220
His interest in band music gave him the idea to
make this song so people can dance to the music.

918
01:21:04,050 --> 01:21:10,110
[It's an American uptempo funky rock song with
rhythmical electric guitar and brass session]

919
01:21:10,110 --> 01:21:19,110
[His interest in band music gave him the idea to
make this song so people can dance to the music]

920
01:21:19,110 --> 01:21:25,160
[With Daybreak and Common Ground as
session members, it gave a fresh sound]

921
01:21:25,160 --> 01:21:31,130
[The concept of a dandy and witty
gambler stood out as well]

922
01:23:19,210 --> 01:23:22,740
"Do You Like That" is also
in the same album.

923
01:23:22,740 --> 01:23:28,880
With his dandy and sexy charm, he
gives an exciting performance.

924
01:23:45,210 --> 01:23:51,100
[A funky rock and roll with a memorable arrangement
of danceable beats and intense band instruments]

925
01:23:51,100 --> 01:23:57,170
[He worked on the lyrics showing off his
exciting performance and sexy charms]

926
01:24:57,550 --> 01:25:05,300
He must be a lucky guy to do a joint performance
with After School at the year-end gayo awards.

927
01:25:05,300 --> 01:25:11,080
A special performance with pretty girls?
To me, he really is a lucky guy.

928
01:25:52,690 --> 01:25:57,850
This is how he creates his
own special colors on stage.

929
01:25:57,850 --> 01:26:04,930
His complete transformation on
stage isn't strange anymore.

930
01:26:04,930 --> 01:26:13,390
Not only is he active in Korea but will solidify his
position as an artist by planning a world tour.

931
01:26:13,390 --> 01:26:18,440
Many are taking interest in
how much he will grow.

